    "body": "Yeah, those are workarounds. But I guess I'm just assuming the .ix() method should work similarly for both Series and DataFrame -- I don't see why the slice would be legal on one but not the other.\n\n   data.ix['a'] #works for both series and Dataframe\n   data.ix[ 'a' , 2 ] #works on both DataFrame and Series\n   data.ix[ : , 2] #works for Series but not DataFrame, as stated above\n   data.ix[ 'a' , : ]  #Works for DataFrame but not Series. (Although easy workaround is just use .ix['a'])\n\nShouldn't the .ix syntax that works for a Series also work for DataFrame?\n"
  },
