    "body": "ix can never go away, or have it's semantics changed due to backcompat. \nNow that @jreback has implemented the new slicing methods to be part of 0.11/\nThe `loc[],iloc[],at[],iat[]` Indexers are available on both frames and series', \nand so now there's also less cause to tinker with ix.\nI would suggest you transition your code to them, I've used them constantly since the\nday they were available.\n\nClosing.\n"
